BEST WAY TO GROW BICEPS IN NO TIME!!!!!
Find a wall and do some strict controlled reps, once you reach failure, take a step ahead and spam as many reps as you can without really worrying about the swings ( OFC don’t over do it ) 

This trick really helps in getting your muscle to failure and beyond which is just the stimulation required for muscle growth, ONLY two sets of these and watch how your biceps blast up. 

Hope this helps

Maybe having been called the big guy in a family function isn’t everything and that’s what I learnt yesterday. I’ve always been the person who neglected yoga or forms of stretching until that lower back injury chose to hit on me. 

I always assumed I was flexible until @rashi.jota proved me wrong. Big thanks to @mcaffeineofficial for this event which made me realise, it’s ‘ inner calm and outer glow ‘ the secret to being a #beactive hero. 
 

[Yoga, Gym, exercise, Motivation, explore ]

Today’s workout routine: 
Seated shoulder press 2x 
Lateral raises 2x
Tricep cable overhead 2x
Chest flies 2x

I prefer alternating between chest dominant push routines and shoulder dominant push routines, this was one of them. A major drawback of PPL is the negligence on secondary muscle groups and I believe this routine gets rid of this issue.

Today’s pull routine:
1. Face pulls 
2. Lat pull down 
3. Seated rows 
4. Bicep cable curls ( 2 sets each ) 

Back days are fun, so are chest days, honestly.. those you think the gym has rude humans, try initially a conversation with the most jacked guy with the hoodie once..He’ll turn out to be the kindest of them all! 

[ Gym, motivation, back day, exercise, pull day, explore ]

Throwback to the leanest I ever was, Although I do not believe in the concept of bulking and cutting, I was here in a significant caloric deficit, eating almost no junk. I weighed 75kgs at that time and I remember the funniest or craziest part was my lunch. My lunch was basically 100gm sweet potato and a scoop of whey isolate. 

Now is it sustainable? No, but a man should achieve that physique atleast once in his lifetime. One should always strive to achieve their potential for him to never be able to achieve it. 
The process of becoming better in and itself brings the best out of you. 

[ Gym, Motivation, Inspiration ]

LEG DAY ROUTINE ( with injured QL- lower back ) 
Hip thrusts 2x 
Leg press 2x
Leg curls 2x 
Calf raises 2x 

Did not really wanted to workout today morning but guess what I did. Honestly, if you think “ jaunga par heavy nahi “ just don’t go at all. Gym poch he gaye ho toh half ass effort kyu dalne? 

Hope this helps! 

[ gym, leg day, workout, motivation, inspiration, morning, exercise, explore ]

Sunday’s PULL routine:
Rear delts 2sets 
Pull ups 100x
Bicep curls 2 sets 

WHAT? THATS IT? Yeah, please understand when I say this, you don’t need to spend half your life at the gym.

To AVOID doing this, STOP making your consumption patterns soo strict, containing barely any carbs just so you lose a couple of pounds on the weighing scale. 

Add in 1-2 cheat meals but make sure you do not overdo and just go bonkers. And yes, A bag of chips is a cheat meal. 

Lift heavy, rest well, stay hard
